Manchester United boss, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, will be without three players when they host Manchester City in the Carabao Cup semi-final fixture on Wednesday night at Old Trafford. The players are Marcos Rojo, Phil Jones and Edinson Cavani. Rojo and Jones have been injured, while Cavani will miss Man United’s clash against Pep Guardiola’s side to suspension. Man United made the announcement in a post via their official website on Tuesday. The Red Devils head to the game after beating Aston Villa 2-1 in their previous fixture in the Premier League last Friday, while Man City defeated Chelsea 3-1. Solskjaer’s side is currently in the second position on the Premier League table with 33 points from 16 games. The kick-off time for Man United vs Man City is 8:45 pm, Nigerian time.